\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

Your most inexcusable sin is the mispronunciation of a word in common,
 every-day use.
 The pronunciation of the word 'municipal,' with the accent on the third syllable,
 is decidedly offensive to an audience of any intellectual stand-ing.
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"-
\end_layout

\end_inset

George Rowland Collins,
 in Platform Speaking.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{displayquote}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do you always accent the second syllables of the following words?
\end_layout

