\begin_layout Standard
Can you pronounce correctly the italicized words in these sentences?
 If in doubt,
 will you please
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 refer to the exercises in pronunciation at the end of Chapters I and II.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 I.
 An inquiry was instituted to determine why the adult was traveling incognito.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 2.
 Each of the municipal employees made a pretense of having a robust pain in his abdomen.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 3.
 The adult told in his address how the museum is financed.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 4.
 After he becomes acclimated,
 he will be more robust physically and more adept at his duties.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 5.
 The order for his discharge was irrevocable.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 6.
 He financed the entire domain.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 7.
 She went to the lyceum in a gondola of incomparable beauty of lines.
