\end_layout

\end_inset

remember that.
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (Pause and let it soak in some more.) 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

The fellow who knocks the cover off the ball or lifts it over the fence for a home run is always the chap who steps up to the plate
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (pause and increase the suspense as to what you are going to say about this extraordinary player) 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

with grim determination in his heart.
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Read the following quotations aloud and with force and meaning.
 Observe where you naturally pause.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

The great American desert is not located in Idaho,
 New Mexico or Arizona.
 It is located under the hat of the average man.
 The great American desert is a mental desert rather than a physical desert.
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"-
\end_layout

\end_inset

J.
 S.
 Knox.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 
