\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

The habitual mispronunciation of such common words as data,
 status,
 and apparatus by speakers is almost unfor-givable.
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"-
\end_layout

\end_inset

George Rowland Collins,
 in Platform Speaking.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\begin_inset Formula $A^{\prime}s$
\end_inset

 which are capitalized in the following should be sounded as 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

 a 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in day:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Tabular
