Men who talk well read more,
 as a rule,
 than the average.
 Without conscious effort,
 they absorb many ideas and the words that express them.
 Something of the style and taste of superior writers gets into their thought and speech.
 Reading is usually considered the most potent single factor in the enlargement of vocabulary.
