Whenever I read a book or a passage that particularly pleased me,
 in which a thing was said or an effect rendered with propriety,
 in which there was either some conspicuous force or some happy distinction in the style,
 I must sit down at once and set myself to ape that quality.
 I was unsuccessful,
 and I knew it;
 and tried again,
 and was again unsuccessful,
 and always unsuccessful;
 but at least in these vain bouts I got some practice in rhythm,
 in harmony,
 in construction and coordination of parts.
