\begin_layout Section*
VOICE EXERCISE-REVIEW
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I.
 Turn to the poem The Cataract of Lodore,
 in Chapter VI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Read this aloud,
 paying especial attention to four things.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 a.
 Be sure that you are breathing from the diaphragm.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 b.
 Be sure that you have a reserve of breath in your lungs to act as a spring board to launch your words to give them carrying power.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 c.
 Be sure that your throat is open and utterly free and relaxed.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 d.
 Be sure that you are using nasal resonance.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 (See Voice Exercise,
 Chapter XIII.) Accentuate the 
\begin_inset Formula $ng$
\end_inset

 sounds that are found in almost every line of this poem.
 Let them ring through your nose.
