The Vagabond,
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

 by Robert Louis Stevenson,
 with the same spirit of happiness singing in your voice that must have sung in Stevenson's heart when he wrote it.
 As we
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 pointed out in the Voice Exercise for Chapter VII,
 the reading of joyous poetry is one of the very best means for developing bright,
 attractive tones.
 
\end_layout

