 he never held an office before in his life.
 He thought that an office was all he needed to be a truly great man,
 and when he came up he adjusted his powerful spectacles and glanced calmly around the audience with amazing dignity.
 Suddenly his eyes fell upon me,
 and then the good old man came right forward and invited me to come up on the stand with the town officers.
 Invited me up on the stand!
 No town officer ever took notice of me before I went to war.
 Now,
