 Then he adjusted his spectacles to be sure that he might see it,
 and walked far back on the platform and then stepped forward like this.
 He must have studied the subject much,
 for he assumed an elocutionary attitude;
 he rested heavily upon his left heel,
 slightly advanced the right foot,
 threw back his shoulders,
 opened the organs of speech,
 and advanced his right hand at an angle of forty-five degrees.
 As he stood in that elocutionary attitude this is just the way that speech went,
 this is it precisely.
 Some of my friends have asked me if I do not exaggerate it,
 but I could not exaggerate it.
 Impossible!
 This is the way it went;
 although I am not here for the story but the lesson that is back of it:
