\begin_layout Standard
A MESSAGE TO GARCIA
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 ELBERT HUBBARD
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is not a speech.
 It originally appeared as an article in the March,
 1899,
 Philistine Magazine.
 It is given here because it is representative of the messages popular in the business world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
About a million and a half copies of this article were distributed by the New York Central Railroad.
 It has been translated into all written languages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the war between Russia and Japan,
 every Russian soldier who went to the front was given a copy of the Message to Garcia.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Japanese,
 finding the booklets in possession of the Russian prisoners,
 concluded that it must be a good thing,
 and accordingly translated it into Japanese.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on an order of the Mikado,
 a copy was given to every man in the employ of the Japanese Government,
 soldier or civilian.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Over forty million copies of A Message to Garcia have been printed.
 This is said to be a larger circulation than any other literary venture has ever attained during the lifetime of the author,
 in all history.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
A MESSAGE TO GARCIA 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In all this Cuban business there is one man stands out on the horizon of my nemory like Mars at Perihelion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When war broke out between Spain and the United States,
 it was very necessary to communicate quickly with the leader of the Insurgents.
 Garcia was somewhere in the mountain fastnesses of Cuba-no one knew where.
 No mail or telegraph message could reach him.
 The President must secure his coöperation,
 and quickly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What to do!
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 Some one said to the President,
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

"
\end_layout

\end_inset

There is a fellow by the name of Rowan will find Garcia for you,
 if anybody can.
