 disappeared into the jungle,
 and in three weeks came out on the other side of the Island,
 having traversed a hostile country on foot,
 and delivered his letter to Garcia-are things I have no special desire now to tell in detail.
 The point that I wish to make is this:
 McKinley gave Rowan a letter to be delivered to Garcia;
 Rowan took the letter and did not ask,
 
