\begin_layout Standard
General Garcia is dead now,
 but there are other Garcias.
 No man who has endeavored to carry out an enterprise where many hands were needed,
 but has been well-nigh appalled at times by the imbecility of the average man-the inability or unwillingness to concentrate on a thing and do it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Slipshod assistance,
 foolish inattention,
 dowdy indifference,
 and half-hearted work seem the rule;
 and no man succeeds,
 unless by hook,
 or crook,
 or threat he forces or bribes other men to assist him;
 or mayhap,
 God in His goodness performs a miracle,
 and sends him an Angel of Light for an assistant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You,
 reader,
